text: @Rusty_SFChron UPDATE: San Francisco will allow indoor hair and nail salons, gyms and hotels to open with limited capacity on Sept. 14, nearly six months after shelter in place orders shuttered them. https://t.co/5BcnPhbAEe

text: @Rusty_SFChron Indoor museum and galleries can open on Sept. 21 after approved health plans, and the city also expects to allow schools to reopen for in-person classes that day with approved safety plans. https://t.co/5BcnPhbAEe

text:
Family and friends are begging for info on the whereabouts of 16-year-old Josiah Williams, who was last seen at home just before the North Complex fires tore through Berry Creek, a rural area in Butte County.

Story by @MeganRCassidy & @AKoseff: https://t.co/aWLiJ2AyPA

name: sfchronicle
text:
President Trump’s order to exclude undocumented immigrants from the census violates long-standing law that requires the population count to include “the whole number of persons in each state,” a federal court ruled.

@BobEgelko has the details here: https://t.co/BqJEFXLxWW

name: sfchronicle
text:
The @49ers say they will pay the $2.7 million September rent for Levi’s Stadium after the Santa Clara Stadium Authority Board voted to authorize a claim for arbitration against the football team for “unpaid facility rent.”

Story by @ByLHernandez: https://t.co/MF8skXYnth
